"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-team-south-africa-involved-in-five-sports-on-saturday-10-august-results-breaking-medal-table\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbTeam South Africa involved in FIVE sports on Saturday, 10 August  Team South Africa are involved in five sports at the 2024 Paris Olympics on Saturday, 10 August as the Games draw to a close.  Team South Africaare involved infivesports at the2024 Paris Olympicson Saturday, 10 August as the Games draw to a close.  Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!  There is an early start with the men's marathon, where Elroy Galant and Stephen Mokoka take to the Paris roads.  There are three further track and field medals up for grabs in the evening session, with Brian Raats (high jump), Jo-Ane van Dyk (javelin) and the Team SA men's 4x400m relay all in action.  Van Dyk and the men's 4x400m are considered possible medal contenders.  The United States (33 golds) lead China (also 33), Australia (18) and Japan (16) in the medal standings.  Team SA are 40th with one gold (Tatjana Smith), two silvers (Smith and men's 4x100m) and two bronzes (men's Sevens rugby and Alan Hatherly).  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  Men's marathon (08:00):Elroy Galant and Stephen Mokoka  Men's high jump, final (19:00): Brian Raats  Women's javelin, final (19:30): Jo-Ane van Dyk  Men's 4x400m, final (21:00): Team SA  Men's kayak single 1000m semi-finals (11:20):Hamish Lovemore  Men's keiren, first round heats (17:31):Jean Spies  Women's individual, fourth round (09:44):Paula Reto is on 227 and tied for 49th after rounds of 78, 73 and 76  Women's individual, fourth round (12:06):Ashleigh Buhai is on 141 after three rounds. She's shot 68, 73 and 74 for 215.  Men's 97kg freestyle, 1/8 final:Nicholas de Lange vs Givi Matcharashvili (Georgia)  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"